b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe29065.htm)  [Next](sbe29067.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n[Buy this Book at\nAmazon.com](http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1421228750/internetsacredte)\n\n* * *\n\n_The Grihya Sutras, Part 1 (SBE29)_ , by Hermann Oldenberg, [1886], at sacred-\ntexts.com\n\n* * *\n\n### KHA _N_ _D_ A 4.\n\n1 1. Now (follows) the \xc3\x82bhyudayika (i.e. the _S_ raddha ceremony referring to\ngood luck).\n\np. 111\n\n2\\. In the fortnight of the increasing moon, on an auspicious day,\n\n3 3. After the sacrifice to the mothers has been performed,\n\n4\\. And an even number of (Brahma _n_ as) versed in the Veda have been invited\nto sit down;\n\n5\\. In the forenoon;\n\n6 6. The rite is performed from left to right.\n\n7 7. The murmuring with the omission of the verses belonging to the Manes.\n\n8\\. The Darbha blades are straight.\n\n9 9. Barley is to be used instead of sesamum.\n\n10\\. The lumps are mixed with curds, jujube fruits, fried grain.\n\n11 11. On inviting (the Manes, he should say), 'The Nandimukha (glad-faced?)\nManes will I invite.'\n\n12 12. 'May the Nandimukha Manes be rejoiced,' instead of 'imperishable.'\n\n13 13. 'The Nandimukha Manes will I make speak,' when he makes (the Brahma _n_\nas) speak.\n\n14 14. '(Was it) well done?'\xc2\x97thus are they to be asked whether they are\nsatiated.\n\np. 112\n\n15\\. The rest is the same (as in the other kinds of _S_ raddha rites), as far\nas it is not [prohibited](errata.htm#0) (by contrary rules).\n\n* * *\n\n### Footnotes\n\n[110:1](sbe29066.htm#fr_243) 4, 1. The \xc3\x82bhyudayika _S_ raddha has to be\nperformed on such p. 111 occasions as the birth of a son, the marriage of a\nson or a daughter, the performance of ceremonies such as the namakarman, _k_ u\n_d_ akarman, &c. See Ya _g_ _\xc3\xb1_ avalkya I, 249.\n\n[111:3](sbe29066.htm#fr_244) A _S_ raddha ceremony directed to the mothers\nhere precedes that consecrated to the fathers.\n\n[111:6](sbe29066.htm#fr_245) Professor Stenzler's translation of Ya _g_ _\xc3\xb1_\navalkya, loc. cit. (pradakshi _n_ av _ri_ tka = die Ehrfurcht beobachtend),\nhas to be corrected according to this Sutra.\n\n[111:7](sbe29066.htm#fr_246) See chap. 1, 8.\n\n[111:9](sbe29066.htm#fr_247) See chap. 1, 3.\n\n[111:11](sbe29066.htm#fr_248) Concerning the invitation' (avahana) see the\nnote on chap. 2, 5.\n\n[111:12](sbe29066.htm#fr_249) See chap. 2, 5 and the note there.\n\n[111:13](sbe29066.htm#fr_250) 'When he causes them to say Svadha.' Naraya _n_\na. Comp. \xc3\x82 _s_ v.-G _ri_ hya IV, 7, 30.\n\n[111:14](sbe29066.htm#fr_251) Comp. chap. 2, 5.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: IV, 5](sbe29067.htm)\n\n"